entries.meaning: The spoken representation of a dash in radio and telegraph Morse code.
(Myanmar) A long knife or sword with a round cross-section grip, a long, gently curving blade with a single edge, and no guard.
examples: Jowar Singh the Sikh procured sabre, quoit, and mace, / Abdul Huq, Wahabi, jerked his dagger from its place, / While amid the jungle-grass danced and grinned and jabbered / Little Boh Hla-oo and cleared his dah-blade from the scabbard.
